==English==

{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Probably a natural expression since it arises across many unrelated languages; for example, Burmese [[ေဟး]] (hei) and Chinese [[哎]] (āi), with similar meanings.

===Pronunciation===
*{{enPR|hā}}, {{IPA|/heɪ/}}, {{SAMPA|/heI/}}
*{{audio|en-us-hey.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Homophones]]: [[hay]]
*:{{rhymes|eɪ}}

===Interjection===
{{en-intj}}

# An exclamation to get [[attention]].
#: '''''Hey''', look at this!''
# A [[protest]] or [[reprimand]].
#: '''''Hey'''! Stop that!''
# An [[expression]] of [[surprise]].
#: '''''Hey'''! This is new!''
# An [[informal]] [[greeting]], similar to [[hi]] (used in the US, Canada and Britain).
#: '''''Hey'''! How's it going?''
# A [[request]] for [[repetition]] or [[explanation]]; an expression of [[confusion]] (see also [[eh]].
#: '''''Hey'''?  How's that?''
# A meaningless [[beat]] [[marker]] or extra, [[filler]] [[syllable]] in music.
#: ''nana na na, '''hey hey hey,''''' good bye

